At first glance, Shopify isn=E2=80=99t an Amazon competitor at all: after a=
ll, there is nothing to buy on Shopify.com. And yet, there were 218 million=
 people that bought products from Shopify without even knowing the company =
existed. The difference is that Shopify is a platform: instead of interfaci=
ng with customers directly, 820,000 3rd-party merchants sit on top of Shopi=
fy and are responsible for acquiring all of those customers on their own.

This means they have to stand out not in a search result on Amazon.com, or =
simply offer the lowest price, but rather earn customers=E2=80=99 attention=
